  "markdown": "[![](https://qsimulate.com/images/nav-bar/logo-light.svg)](https://qsimulate.com/home)\n  * [Home](https://qsimulate.com/home)\n  * [Products](https://qsimulate.com/products)\n  * [Technology](https://qsimulate.com/technology)\n  * [About Us](https://qsimulate.com/about-us)\n  * [News](https://qsimulate.com/news)\n  * [Careers](https://qsimulate.com/careers)\n  * [Other](https://qsimulate.com/other)\n  * [Get in Touch ![](https://qsimulate.com/images/home/learn-arrow.svg)](https://qsimulate.com/#info)\n\u00a92022 QSimulate, All rights reserved.\n\n\nBy using qsimulate.com, you agree to the use of cookies and our[cookie policy](https://qsimulate.com/cookies).\nOK\n# DOE Supports a Joint Project Between QSimulate, Caltech, IBM, and Others\n![](https://qsimulate.com/images/news/articles/article-calendar-icon.svg)\nMarch 13, 2026\n![](https://qsimulate.com/images/news/articles/article-37.png)\nQSimulate is proud to announce that our project with Caltech (Profs. Sandeep Sharma and Garnet Chan), IBM, and other partners has been selected for funding by U.S. Department of Energy (DOE) ARPA-E through their QC3 program.  \n  \nThe project, entitled \u201cQuantum Algorithms for Accelerated Discovery of Bioelectrocatalytic Materials for Nitrogen Fixation,\u201d will be led by Caltech and will support our collaboration on quantum algorithm development.  \n  \nWe look forward to the collaboration!\n[Read More >](https://arpa-e.energy.gov/news-and-events/news-and-insights/us-department-energy-announces-37-million-develop-quantum-computing-drive-exponential-advances-chemistry-and-materials-science)[< Return to News](https://qsimulate.com/news/1/)\n  * ![](https://qsimulate.com/images/nav-bar/logo-light.svg)\n  * \u00a92022 QSimulate, All rights reserved.\n\n\n  * Get In Touch\n  * ![](https://qsimulate.com/images/nav-bar/email.svg)info@qsimulate.com\n  * ![](https://qsimulate.com/images/nav-bar/phone.svg)+1-(617)249-4828\n  * 20 Guest St, STE 101, Boston, MA 02135, USA\n  * [![](https://qsimulate.com/images/about/team-linkedin-gray.svg)LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/qsimulate/)\n\n\n  * Site Map\n  * [Home](https://qsimulate.com/home)\n  * [Products](https://qsimulate.com/products)\n  * [Technology](https://qsimulate.com/technology)\n  * [About Us](https://qsimulate.com/about-us)\n  * [News](https://qsimulate.com/news)\n  * [Careers](https://qsimulate.com/careers)\n  * [Other](https://qsimulate.com/other)\n\n\n  * User Policies\n  * [Terms & Conditions](https://qsimulate.com/terms)\n  * [Privacy Policy](https://qsimulate.com/privacy)\n  * [Cookie Policy](https://qsimulate.com/cookies)\n  * [FCOI Policy](https://qsimulate.com/files/policies/fcoi_policy.pdf)\n\n\n",
